Question:
Compute the average of all numbers in a list.
Input:
List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(3, 6, 9, 12);

Solutions:

Java 8 Streams compute average using mapToInt.average(). For input [3, 6, 9, 12], average 7.5.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Stream list via stream(). Convert to IntStream with mapToInt(Integer::intValue). Call average() for OptionalDouble.

#Java Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public class ComputeAverage {
    public static void printAverage(List<Integer> numbers) {
        numbers.stream()
               .mapToInt(Integer::intValue)
               .average()
               .ifPresent(System.out::println);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<Integer> list = Arrays.asList(3, 6, 9, 12);
        printAverage(list);
    }
}

Prints 7.5. OptionalDouble.ifPresent safe for empty.

#Thought Process
mapToInt unboxes efficiently. average() divides sum by count as double. Handles empty via OptionalDouble. Alternatives: reduce manual avg; average() optimized.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty list: No print (OptionalDouble.empty()).
Null list: NPE.
Null elements: NPE on intValue; filter.
Zeroes: 0.0.
Negatives: Correct avg.
